description:
Pierre Theriault aka "Art-Machine" and "TheRealT!" got his start in comics over 10 years ago, spending many years as colorist at Dreamwave and Udon comics, freelancing for Marvel, Image, DC. He worked on various titles including the Transformers: Armada as lead colorist, followed by some time on Street Fighter.

He eventually made the transition to gaming as texture artist at Ubisoft. He eventually became a senior texture artist, and senior model/texture artist on next gen projects. Some of his titles include Surf's Up, Rainbow Six Vegas 2 and James Cameron's Avatar:The Game (PS3/PC/360).

He is currently working on an independent projects.
name: TheRealT!
